{"title_page": "Marc Gomez", "text_new": "{{short description|French cyclist}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name          = Marc Gomez\n| image         =\n| fullname      = Marc Gomez\n| nickname      =\n| birth_date    = {{Birth date and age|1954|9|19|df=y}}\n| birth_place   = [[Rennes]], [[France]]\n| height        =\n| weight        =\n| currentteam   =\n| discipline    = Road\n| role          = Rider\n| ridertype     =\n| amateuryears1 =\n| amateurteam1  =\n| proyears1     = 1982&ndash;1983\n| proteam1      = Wolber\n| proyears2     = 1984&ndash;1985\n| proteam2      = La Vie Claire\n| proyears3     = 1986&ndash;1987\n| proteam3      = Reynolds\n| proyears4     = 1988\n| proteam4      = Fagor\n| proyears5     = 1989\n| proteam5      = Reynolds\n| majorwins     = Milan\u2013San Remo (1982)<br />Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a, 3 stages <br> French National Road Race Champion (1983)\n}}\n'''Marc Gomez''' (born 19 September 1954 in [[Rennes]]) is a [[France|French]] former professional [[road bicycle racer]]. He has Spanish heritage, as his parents were born in [[Torrelavega]] ([[Spain]]). He was a professional from 1982 until 1989.\n\n== Palmar\u00e8s ==\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n; 1979\n: 1st, [[Bordeaux-Saintes]]\n\n; 1981\n: 1st, Bordeaux-Saintes\n: 3rd, National Road Championships, Amateurs\n\n; 1982\n: 1st, Camors\n: 1st, Langolen\n: 1st, [[Milan\u2013San Remo]]\n: [[1982 Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a|Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a]]\n:: 1st, Prologue\n:: 3rd, Stage 2\n:: 3rd, Stage 3\n\n; 1983\n: 1st, National Road Championships\n\n; 1984\n: 1st, Lanester\n\n; 1985\n: 1st, Overall, [[Postgirot Open]]\n:: 1st, Stage 1\n:: 3rd, Stage 8\n: 1st, Stage 3 [[Tour de France]] (team time trial)\n\n; 1986\n: [[1986 Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a|Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a]]\n:: 1st, Stage 2\n:: 1st, Stage 20\n\n; 1988\n: 1st, [[Bordeaux-Cauderan]]\n: 1st, Stage 4a, [[Vuelta a la Communidad Valenciana]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{cycling archives|6665}}\n\n{{Milan\u2013San Remo winners}}\n{{French National Road Race Championships (men)}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gomez, Marc}}\n[[Category:French male cyclists]]\n[[Category:French Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a stage winners]]\n[[Category:1954 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Rennes]]\n[[Category:Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a cyclists]]\n{{France-cycling-bio-1950s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox cyclist\n| name          = Marc Gomez\n| image         =\n| fullname      = Marc Gomez\n| nickname      =\n| birth_date    = {{Birth date and age|1954|9|19|df=y}}\n| birth_place   = [[Rennes]], [[France]]\n| height        =\n| weight        =\n| currentteam   =\n| discipline    = Road\n| role          = Rider\n| ridertype     =\n| amateuryears1 =\n| amateurteam1  =\n| proyears1     = 1982&ndash;1983\n| proteam1      = Wolber\n| proyears2     = 1984&ndash;1985\n| proteam2      = La Vie Claire\n| proyears3     = 1986&ndash;1987\n| proteam3      = Reynolds\n| proyears4     = 1988\n| proteam4      = Fagor\n| proyears5     = 1989\n| proteam5      = Reynolds\n| majorwins     = Milan\u2013San Remo (1982)<br />Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a, 3 stages <br> French National Road Race Champion (1983)\n}}\n'''Marc Gomez''' (born 19 September 1954 in [[Rennes]]) is a [[France|French]] former professional [[road bicycle racer]]. He has Spanish heritage, as his parents were born in [[Torrelavega]] ([[Spain]]). He was a professional from 1982 until 1989.\n\n== Palmar\u00e8s ==\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n; 1979\n: 1st, [[Bordeaux-Saintes]]\n\n; 1981\n: 1st, Bordeaux-Saintes\n: 3rd, National Road Championships, Amateurs\n\n; 1982\n: 1st, Camors\n: 1st, Langolen\n: 1st, [[Milan\u2013San Remo]]\n: [[1982 Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a|Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a]]\n:: 1st, Prologue\n:: 3rd, Stage 2\n:: 3rd, Stage 3\n\n; 1983\n: 1st, National Road Championships\n\n; 1984\n: 1st, Lanester\n\n; 1985\n: 1st, Overall, [[Postgirot Open]]\n:: 1st, Stage 1\n:: 3rd, Stage 8\n: 1st, Stage 3 [[Tour de France]] (team time trial)\n\n; 1986\n: [[1986 Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a|Vu