{"title_page": "Do Not Disturb (Bananarama song)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2019}}\n{{Use British English|date=May 2019}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Do Not Disturb\n| cover      = Banana_dnd.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Bananarama]]\n| album      = [[True Confessions (album)|True Confessions]]\n| B-side     = Ghost\n| released   = 12 August 1985 <small>(UK)</small><ref>{{cite web|url=http://i.imgur.com/0yIJWmD.jpg|title='Do Not Disturb' UK promotional advertisement|publisher=[[Imgur]]|accessdate=2016-01-05}}</ref>\n| format     = 7\" single, 12\" single\n| recorded   = April 1985\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Pop music|Pop]]\n| length     = 3:25\n| label      = [[London Records]]\n| writer     = [[Jolley & Swain]]\n| producer   = Jolley & Swain\n| prev_title = [[Hot Line To Heaven]]\n| prev_year  = 1984\n| next_title = [[Venus_(Shocking_Blue_song)#Bananarama_version|Venus]]\n| next_year  = 1986\n}}\n\"'''Do Not Disturb'''\" is a song recorded by English [[girl group]] [[Bananarama]].  It was written and produced by the production duo of [[Jolley & Swain|Steve Jolley and Tony Swain]].  Originally released as a stand-alone single in 1985, the track was later added to Bananarama's third album ''[[True Confessions (album)|True Confessions]]'' which was issued by [[London Records]] a year later.  \"Do Not Disturb\" was released in the UK, Australia, Germany and Japan but only charted in the UK.\n\nBananarama did not like the song.  Group member [[Keren Woodward]] later said of the ''True Confessions'' album, \"It is all our ideas, it is what we wanted to sound like and sing about. Except 'Do Not Disturb' which Swain and Jolley wrote and which we don't think is very good. Thats why there's eleven songs on the LP instead of ten\".<ref>{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061029193507/http://www.bananaramauk.com/html/discography/singles/donotdisturb/dndmain.html|url=http://www.bananaramauk.com/html/discography/singles/donotdisturb/dndmain.html|title=Do Not Disturb|publisher=bananarama.co.uk|archivedate=2006-10-29|accessdate=2016-01-05}}</ref>  When released, \"Do Not Disturb\" was a mid-charting single, peaking at number thirty-one.\n\nThe song was also issued as 3 separate shaped picture discs, each featuring a member of the group, which came with a plinth to put them on display.\n\n==Music video==\n\nThe [[music video]] for \"Do Not Disturb\" directed by Simon Milne features Bananarama in a brightly lit hotel clad in long white flowing dresses and blouses similar to the single's picture sleeve. The video also cuts frequently to a set with Bananarama dancing, and doing [[Association football|football]] tricks with superimposed circular footage. The whole video has a \"round\" theme, from round beds, and spas to a round frame in which each member dances within.\n\n==Track listings==\n;UK 7\" vinyl single \n''London Records NANA 9''\n#\"Do Not Disturb\"  3:23\n#\"Ghost\"  4:03\n#:<small>P. Bishop/P. Seymour/S. Dallin</small>\n+ Some versions of the 7 inch were released in 3 different shaped picture disc singles format ''NANPD 9''\n\n;UK 12\" vinyl single \n''London Records NANX 9''\n#\"Do Not Disturb\" (12\" Version)  6:08\n#\"Do Not Disturb\" (Dub)  3:43\n#\"Ghost\"  4:03\n\n;2nd UK 12\" vinyl single \n''London Records NANAM 9''\n#\"Do Not Disturb\" (12\" Version)  6:08\n#\"Ghost\"  4:03\n#\"Do Not Disturb\" (Bananamix)  10:50 +\n\n+ A megamix featuring 6 of their earlier hits\n\n== Charts ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!align=\"left\"|Chart (1985)\n!align=\"left\"|Peak<br>position\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|[[UK Singles Chart]]<ref name=occ>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/30294/bananarama/|title=Official Charts > Bananarama|publisher=The Official UK Charts Company|accessdate=2016-01-05}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|31\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{MetroLyrics song|bananarama|do-not-disturb}}<!-- Licensed lyrics provider -->\n\n{{Bananarama}}\n\n[[Category:1985 singles]]\n[[Category:Bananarama songs]]\n[[Category:London Records singles]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Tony Swain (musician)]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Steve Jolley (songwriter)]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Jolley & Swain]]\n[[Category:1985 songs]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2019}}\n{{Use British English|date=May 2019}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Do Not Disturb\n| cover      = Banana_dnd.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Bananarama]]\n| album      = [[True Confessions (album)|True Confessions]]\n| B-side     = Ghost\n| released   = 12 August 1985 <small>(UK)</small><ref>{{cite web|url=http://i.imgur.com/0yIJWmD.jpg|title='Do Not Disturb' UK promotional advertisement|publisher=[[Imgur]]|accessdate=2016-01-05}}</ref>\n| format     = 7\" single, 12\" single\n| recorded   = April 1985\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Pop music|Pop]]\n| length     = 3:25\n| label      = [[London Records]]\n| writer     = [[Jolley & Swain]]\n| producer   = Jolley & Swain\n| prev_title = [[The Wild Life (Bananarama song)|The Wild Life]]\n| prev_year  = 1984\n| next_title = [[Venus_(Shocking_Blue_song)#Bananarama_version|Venus]]\n| next_year  = 1986\n}}\n\"'''Do Not Disturb'''\" is a song recorded by English [[girl group]] [[Bananarama]].  It was written and produced by the production duo of [[Jolley & Swain|Steve Jolley and Tony Swain]].  Originally released as a stand-alone single in 1985, the track was later added to Bananarama's third album ''[[True Confessions (album)|True Confessions]]'' which was issued by [[London Records]] a year later.  \"Do Not Disturb\" was released in the UK, Australia, Germany and Japan but only charted in the UK.\n\nBananarama did not like the song.  Group member [[Keren Woodward]] later said of the ''True Confessions'' album, \"It is all our ideas, it is what we wanted to sound like and sing about. Except 'Do Not Disturb' which Swain and Jolley wrote and which we don't think is very good. Thats why there's eleven songs on the LP instead of ten\".<ref>{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061029193507/http://www.bananaramauk.com/html/discography/singles/donotdisturb/dndmain.html|url=http://www.bananaramauk.com/html/discography/singles/donotdisturb/dndmain.html|title=Do Not Disturb|publisher=bananarama.co.uk|archivedate=2006-10-29|accessdate=2016-01-05}}</ref>  When released, \"Do Not Disturb\" was a mid-charting single, peaking at number thirty-one.\n\nThe song was also issued as 3 separate shaped picture discs, each featuring a member of the group, which came with a plinth to put them on display.\n\n==Music video==\n\nThe [[music video]] for \"Do Not Disturb\" directed by Simon Milne features Bananarama in a brightly lit hotel clad in long white flowing dresses and blouses similar to the single's picture sleeve. The video also cuts frequently to a set with Bananarama dancing, and doing [[Association football|football]] tricks with superimposed circular footage. The whole video has a \"round\" theme, from round beds, and spas to a round frame in which each member dances within.\n\n==Track listings==\n;UK 7\" vinyl single \n''London Records NANA 9''\n#\"Do Not Disturb\"  3:23\n#\"Ghost\"  4:03\n#:<small>P. Bishop/P. Seymour/S. Dallin</small>\n+ Some versions of the 7 inch were released in 3 different shaped picture disc singles format ''NANPD 9''\n\n;UK 12\" vinyl single \n''London Records NANX 9''\n#\"Do Not Disturb\" (12\" Version)  6:08\n#\"Do Not Disturb\" (Dub)  3:43\n#\"Ghost\"  4:03\n\n;2nd UK 12\" vinyl single \n''London Records NANAM 9''\n#\"Do Not Disturb\" (12\" Version)  6:08\n#\"Ghost\"  4:03\n#\"Do Not Disturb\" (Bananamix)  10:50 +\n\n+ A megamix featuring 6 of their earlier hits\n\n== Charts ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!align=\"left\"|Chart (1985)\n!align=\"left\"|Peak<br>position\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|[[UK Singles Chart]]<ref name=occ>{{cite web|url=http